description.plain:
Kanye West and Ty Dolla $ign wear their hearts on their sleeves in “KEYS TO MY LIFE.” Assisted by India Love, the duo sum up ins and outs of unhealthy relationships, displaying what shouldn’t happen in strong ones.

Ye specifically details the end of his marriage to socialite Kim Kardashian, which was broke off in 2022. His verses open himself up to his newly-wed partner, Bianca Censori, which is encapsulated by India Love’s outro giving her partner “the keys to [her] life.”

“KEYS TO MY LIFE” was originally titled “Timbo Freestyle,” placed as the eighth track on a tentative tracklist of VULTURES, and debuted at a private listening party on December 15, 2023 in Las Vegas. Afterward, it removed India Love’s presence, though aptly re-added her outro in time for the VULTURES listening party on February 8, 2024.
